# Comparison vs benchmarks/baseline/post-aggressive-opts.log:
#
#   latticeThreeStagePipelineFused:    28.96 M -> 43.33 M ops/s   (+50%, source-inline fusion)
#   latticeThreeStagePipelinePhysical: 28.99 M -> 41.93 M ops/s   (+45%, trusted fast-path emit)
#   latticeSpscPreallocated:           31.71 M -> 39.11 M ops/s   (+23%, trusted fast-path emit)
#
# The "physical" pipeline gains come entirely from routing SourceEmitter.emit through the
# trusted fast-path (no handle / no stamping) and from changing MPSC consumer self-loads to
# opaque reads. The fused gain on top of that is the inline source-side fusion bypassing the
# SPSC ring on the producer thread.
#
# Lattice now materially beats Disruptor on the physical-three-stage pipeline (42M vs 32M)
# and is within 12% of Disruptor's hand-fused single-thread chain (43M vs 49M) for the
# logical-stages-still-visible Lattice fused pipeline. As documented in the README, primitive
# SPSC and MPSC queue shapes still favor Disruptor and we do not target them as headline cases.

